The Model of the Matching Market
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section, I lay out a model of a matching market that will allow
 me to evaluate how information disclosure policy affects the equilibrium
 market outcome.
 The model has two main components: the matching process between buyers
 and sellers, and the seller optimization problem.
 At the end of this section, I define the steady-state equilibrium, in which
 seller actions are individually optimal and the dynamic matching system
 is in a steady state.
 
\end_layout

